{
  "texts": [
    "Their approach involved enhancing the FLT3 selectivity of a previously active molecule against breast cancer cells, which was predicted to interact with FLT3.",
    "A deep learning generative model was trained on drug-like SMILES structures and fine-tuned with known FLT3 binders.",
    "The model generated over 10,000 structures.",
    "These were filtered, and the resulting molecules were ranked based on their binding affinities derived from Alchemical Free Energy calculations.",
    "The most promising compound was synthesized and tested in cellular cultures and on the protein."
  ]
}